cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CL 

The paper discusses the evaluation of graph neural networks (GNNs) for semi-supervised node classification in graphs, which is a problem in machine learning and data mining. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the shortcomings of existing evaluation strategies, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
